## Conclusion

The Credit Card Approval Prediction System demonstrates the effective use of machine learning to automate the credit card approval process. The project analyzes applicant information such as income, employment status, family status, housing type, and credit history to predict whether a credit card application should be approved or rejected.

The system follows a complete machine learning workflow, including data preprocessing, feature engineering, model training, testing, and evaluation. Multiple classification algorithms were compared, and the best-performing model was selected based on its prediction accuracy.

The selected model was integrated into a Flask web application, allowing users to enter applicant details and receive instant prediction results. IBM Watson Machine Learning was also used for cloud deployment, enabling scalable and real-time prediction.

Overall, this project demonstrates the practical application of machine learning, Flask, and cloud technologies in solving a real-world financial problem by improving the efficiency, accuracy, and consistency of the credit card approval process.
